Reasoning: The paper discusses algorithms for analogy and high-level perception, which are common topics in natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. The use of machine learning techniques and feature vectors also suggests a focus on computational linguistics (CL) and machine learning (LG). The paper's application to tests of word comprehension further supports its classification under CL and AI. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI and cs.LG. The use of supervised machine learning techniques also suggests a possible classification under cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
